# Generation Instructions for CLAUDE.md

## Context

You are generating the root onboarding file (CLAUDE.md) for the project. This file serves as the **first point of contact** for AI assistants (like Claude Code) when they start working on the project.

This file should:
- Introduce the Memory Bank documentation system
- Provide high-level project overview
- List key documents to start with
- Describe available AI agents
- Set expectations for how AI assistants should work with the project

**Audience**: AI assistants (primary), human developers (secondary)
**Tone**: Professional, welcoming, instructive
**Length**: 50-100 lines

## Input Data

You have access to the following project data:

```json
{
  "project_name": "string",
  "project_type": "web_app|api|mobile_app|cli|library|other",
  "project_description": "string",

  "backend_framework": "string|null",
  "frontend_framework": "string|null",
  "database": "string|null",

  "is_monorepo": true|false,
  "backend_dir": "string",
  "frontend_dir": "string|null",

  "has_frontend": true|false,
